brainly_data.question: When 415 junior college students were surveyed, 150 said they have a passport. constructa 95% confidence interval for the proportion of junior college students that have apassport. round to the nearest thousandth?
brainly_data.subject: Mathematics

all_answers.question: When 415 junior college students were surveyed, 150 said they have a passport. constructa 95% confidence interval for the proportion of junior college students that have apassport. round to the nearest thousandth?
all_answers.subject: Mathematics
all_answers.text:
Solution:
The 95% confident interval will be estimated as follows:

sample proportion: 150/415=0.362

ME=1.96*[0.362*0.638/415]=0.0011
thus
95% CI
0.362-0.0011<p<0.362+0.0011
